rComments: Good prof. Makes MAT237 easier and doable.

The tag say lectures are long, they're not actually (1-2 hours), but they feel a hell of a lot longer. He explains everything right down to every last detail and provides a boatload of examples. This may be good for some people, but for me, it was a drag; very boring.  His monotonicity didn't help.

Very helpful professor, don't understand the negativity towards him. If you do the problem sets he assigned and listen to lecture carefully, nothing is hard at all in this course, final exams are the same questions from midterms just with numbers changed. Overall, not hard to get good mark, haters gonna hate.
teacherRatingTags: ['Inspirational', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Clear grading criteria']
